<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Asimov proposes that the human cannot comprehend total darkness if it has never experienced that condition. In the story, we encounter a civilization <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Asimov proposes that the human cannot comprehend total darkness if it has never experienced that condition. In the story, we encounter a civilization completely unfamiliar with darkness. Having 6 suns and a full eclipse only once every thousand years, generations come and go knowing only daylight, never what we know as night. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
